how much your body changes after the second pregnancy hi girls after my first and the only pregnancy so far i developed saggy breasts a few stretch marks on my butt and stomach weak bladder and a little bit fat left on my stomach looks like old skin with wrinkles so i have planned to have another baby but would like to ask from your experience ladies how much do you change after second pregnancy do you look and feel even times worse than after the first pregnancy and what changed so much my first i was producing litres of milk a day i went from a b to a dd then when i stopped breast feeding lost it all and now even after a second pregnancy i have what i call ethiopian t ts a few stretch marks on the top of my thighs groin area and on my breasts i lost weight quite quickly after my first losing more weight than what i had gained i was terrified about having another baby as everyone had told me that it was harder to lose weight the second time around and i may not even lose any well i seem to be an exception to the rule in just about everything not only did i lose all of the baby weight and then some but i did it in less than a month the joys of breast feeding really do pay off that was years ago and now i can't seem to gain any weight my body didn't change that much after either of my pregnancies every woman is different though the only thing that dramatically changed with me was my chest i am now down to a a b the one miracle that i can hold on to is that i do not have any cellulite i count my lucky stars on this one have a great day night x k Breastfeeding Pregnancy Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Urinary incontinence Puberty Milk EastEnders Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Breast Professional wrestling holds Brassiere Doxepin Tocopherol Stomach cancer Childbirth Professional wrestling attacks Obstetrics Adjustable gastric band Fat fetishism Abortion debate Guinea pig Premature birth Elephant Spina bifida Breast cancer Breast milk Pregnancy fetishism Conker's Bad Fur Day